{"title":"If There Is Something to Desire, 9, 17, 18","author":{"name":"Vera Pavlova"},"publishDate":"2011-10-01","lines":[{"line":"9","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"I broke your heart.","stanza":2,"number":2},{"line":"Now barefoot I tread","stanza":2,"number":3},{"line":"on shards.","stanza":2,"number":4},{"line":"17","stanza":3,"number":5},{"line":"Why is the word yes so brief?","stanza":4,"number":6},{"line":"It should be","stanza":4,"number":7},{"line":"the longest,","stanza":4,"number":8},{"line":"the hardest,","stanza":4,"number":9},{"line":"so that you could not decide in an instant to say it,","stanza":4,"number":10},{"line":"so that upon reflection you could stop","stanza":4,"number":11},{"line":"in the middle of saying it.","stanza":4,"number":12},{"line":"18","stanza":5,"number":13},{"line":"—Sing me The Song of Songs.","stanza":6,"number":14},{"line":"—Don’t know the words.","stanza":6,"number":15},{"line":"—Then sing the notes.","stanza":6,"number":16},{"line":"—Don’t know the notes.","stanza":6,"number":17},{"line":"—Then simply hum.","stanza":6,"number":18},{"line":"—Forgot the tune.","stanza":6,"number":19},{"line":"—Then press my ear","stanza":6,"number":20},{"line":"to your ear","stanza":6,"number":21},{"line":"and sing what you hear.","stanza":6,"number":22}]}